<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910401-0060</DOCNO><DOCID>910401-0060.</DOCID><HL>   Loral to Get Major Contract   For F-16 Electronics Gear</HL><DATE>04/01/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B2</SO><CO>   LOR GD MD FREST</CO><IN>AEROSPACE (ARO)</IN><LP>   NEW YORK -- Loral Corp. said it will get more than $100million of work providing aircraft warning receivers for 120F-16 jet fighters South Korea has agreed to buy from GeneralDynamics Corp.   &quot;In effect, General Dynamics made its proposal to theKoreans including the electronic warfare suite, and that's alittle unusual,&quot; said Bernard L. Schwartz, chairman and chiefexecutive officer of Loral, a defense-electronics concern.</LP><TEXT>   General Dynamics won the $5.2 billion order last week,beating out rival aerospace giant McDonnell Douglas Corp.,which had hoped to sell its F/A18 jets to the Koreans.   Mr. Schwartz said the General Dynamics agreement includesoptions for the purchase of Loral electronic jammers for theF-16s, which could add another $200 million or more of workfor Loral. &quot;This would be the first time this radar warningreceiver and this particular jammer are configured in thesame system,&quot; he said.</TEXT></DOC>